<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{y}=-{51}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}-{y}={35}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},-{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{1}{y}=-{51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}=-{51}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{51}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{\left(\frac{{-{51}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}}}{{6}}\right)}+-{1}{y}={35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{4}}{{6}}\cdot{\left(-{51}\right)}--\frac{{4}}{{6}}{\left({1}\right)}{y}+-{1}{y}={35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{34}-{\left({0.66666666666667}\right)}{y}+-{1}{y}={35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.66666666666667}{y}+{\left(-{1}\right)}{y}={35}-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.66666666666667}{y}+{\left(-{1}\right)}{y}={1}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({0.66666666666667}+{\left(-{1}\right)}\right)}{y}={1}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.33333333333333}{y}={1}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{1}}{{-{{0.33333333333333}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{1}{\left(-{3}\right)}=-{51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{\left(-{3}\right)}=-{51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}=-{51}-{\left(-{3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}=-{48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{48}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},-{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

